{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:proverbs.1",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 1,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 1 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:1",
      "text": "The parables of Solomon, the son of David, king of Israel,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:2",
      "text": "To know wisdom, and instruction:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:3",
      "text": "To understand the words of prudence: and to receive the instruction of doctrine, justice, and judgment, and equity:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:4",
      "text": "To give subtilty to little ones, to the young man knowledge and understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:5",
      "text": "A wise man shall hear, and shall be wiser: and he that understandeth shall possess governments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:6",
      "text": "He shall understand a parable and the interpretation, the words of the wise, and their mysterious sayings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:7",
      "text": "The fear of the Lord is the beginning of wisdom. Fools despise wisdom and instruction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:8",
      "text": "My son, hear the instruction of thy father, and forsake not the law of thy mother:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:9",
      "text": "That grace may be added to thy head, and a chain of gold to thy neck.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:10",
      "text": "My son, if sinners shall entice thee, consent not to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:11",
      "text": "If they shall say: Come with us, let us lie in wait for blood, let us hide snares for the innocent without cause:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:12",
      "text": "Let us swallow him up alive like hell, and whole as one that goeth down into the pit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:13",
      "text": "We shall find all precious substance, we shall fill our houses with spoils.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:14",
      "text": "Cast in thy lot with us, let us all have one purse.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:15",
      "text": "My son, walk not thou with them, restrain thy foot from their paths.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:16",
      "text": "For their feet run to evil, and make haste to shed blood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:17",
      "text": "But a net is spread in vain before the eyes of them that have wings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:18",
      "text": "And they themselves lie in wait for their own blood, and practise deceits against their own souls.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:19",
      "text": "So the ways of every covetous man destroy the souls of the possessors.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:20",
      "text": "Wisdom preacheth abroad, she uttereth her voice in the streets:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:21",
      "text": "At the head of multitudes she crieth out, in the entrance of the gates of the city she uttereth her words, saying:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:22",
      "text": "O children, how long will you love childishness, and fools covet those things which are hurtful to themselves, and the unwise hate knowledge?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:23",
      "text": "Turn ye at my reproof: behold I will utter my spirit to you, and will shew you my words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:24",
      "text": "Because I called, and you refused: I stretched out my hand, and there was none that regarded.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:25",
      "text": "You have despised all my counsel, and have neglected my reprehensions.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:26",
      "text": "I also will laugh in your destruction, and will mock when that shall come to you which you feared.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:27",
      "text": "When sudden calamity shall fall on you, and destruction, as a tempest, shall be at hand: when tribulation and distress shall come upon you:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:28",
      "text": "Then shall they call upon me, and I will not hear: they shall rise in the morning, and shall not find me:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:29",
      "text": "Because they have hated instruction, and received not the fear of the Lord,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:30",
      "text": "Nor consented to my counsel, but despised all my reproof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:31",
      "text": "Therefore they shall eat the fruit of their own way, and shall be filled with their own devices.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.32",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:32",
      "text": "The turning away of little ones shall kill them, and the prosperity of fools shall destroy them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.1.33",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 1:33",
      "text": "But he that shall hear me, shall rest without terror, and shall enjoy abundance, without fear of evils.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
